article.headline: St. Francis, Pa. 66, Youngstown St. 65
article.story: YOUNGSTOWN, Ohio -- Cale Nelson hit a jumper and two free throws in the last minute for St. Francis, Pa., to ensure a 66-65 win over Youngstown State Saturday night. St. Francis (2-4) built a 12-point lead by halftime and led in single digits throughout the second half. Marquis Ford's layup with 2:42 left put the Red Flash ahead 62-56. DeAndre Mays made a 3-pointer on Youngstown State's next possession, but Nelson followed with his jumper about a minute later. Vytas Sulskis made two 3-pointers in the final minute for the Penguins (1-4), but Nelson's two free throws were enough to keep St. Francis in front. Mislav Jukic scored 15 points, Grant Suprenant had 14, Ford added 12 and Devin Sweetney 11 for St. Francis. Nelson added nine points and five assists. Sulskis scored 22 points and Sirlester Martin had 11 points and nine rebounds for Youngstown State.
